<section xml:id="C30.S11">
<title>Radial Spheroidal Wave Functions</title>        
   
<subsection xml:id="C30.S11.SS1">
<title>Definitions</title>        
 
       
<para xml:id="C30.S11.SS1.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="1" xml:id="C30.S11.SS1.p1.s1">
Denote <Math equation-number="30.11.1" mode="display" xml:id="C30.S11.E1">\psi_{k}^{(j)}(z)=\left(\frac{\pi}{2z}\right)^{\frac{1}{2}}{\cal C}_{k+\frac{1 }{2}}^{(j)}(z), if j=1,2,3,4,</Math> where <Math equation-number="30.11.2" mode="display" xml:id="C30.S11.E2">{\cal C}_{\nu}^{(1)}=J_{\nu},{\cal C}_{\nu}^{(2)}=Y_{\nu},{\cal C}_{\nu}^{(3)}={H^{(1)}_{\nu}},{\cal C}_{\nu}^{(4)}={H^{(2)}_{\nu}},</Math> with <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C30.S11.SS1.p1.m1">J_{\nu}</Math> , <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C30.S11.SS1.p1.m2">Y_{\nu}</Math> , <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C30.S11.SS1.p1.m3">{H^{(1)}_{\nu}}</Math> , and <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C30.S11.SS1.p1.m4">{H^{(2)}_{\nu}}</Math> as in §10.2(ii).
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="2" xml:id="C30.S11.SS1.p1.s2">
Then solutions of (30.2.1) with <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C30.S11.SS1.p1.m5">\mu=m</Math> and <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C30.S11.SS1.p1.m6">\lambda=\lambda^{m}_{n}\left(\gamma^{2}\right)</Math> are given by <Math equation-number="30.11.3" mode="display" xml:id="C30.S11.E3">S^{m(j)}_{n}\left(z,\gamma\right)=\frac{(1-z^{-2})^{\frac{1}{2}m}}{A_{n}^{-m}( \gamma^{2})}\sum_{2k\geq m-n}a^{-m}_{n,k}(\gamma^{2})\psi_{n+2k}^{(j)}(\gamma z)</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="3" sentence-num-in-section="3" xml:id="C30.S11.SS1.p1.s3">
Here <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C30.S11.SS1.p1.m7">a^{-m}_{n,k}(\gamma^{2})</Math> is defined by (30.8.2) and (30.8.6), and <Math equation-number="30.11.4" mode="display" xml:id="C30.S11.E4">A_{n}^{\pm m}(\gamma^{2})=\sum_{2k\geq\mp m-n}(-1)^{k}a^{\pm m}_{n,k}(\gamma^{ 2})\quad(\neq 0)</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="4" sentence-num-in-section="4" xml:id="C30.S11.SS1.p1.s4">
In (30.11.3)
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="5" sentence-num-in-section="5" xml:id="C30.S11.SS1.p1.s5">
<Math mode="inline" xml:id="C30.S11.SS1.p1.m8">z\neq 0</Math> when <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C30.S11.SS1.p1.m9">j=1</Math> , and <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C30.S11.SS1.p1.m10">|z|&gt;1</Math> when <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C30.S11.SS1.p1.m11">j=2,3,4</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
<paragraph xml:id="C30.S11.Px1">
<title>Connection Formulas</title>    
<para xml:id="C30.S11.Px1.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="6" xml:id="C30.S11.Px1.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="30.11.5" mode="display" xml:id="C30.S11.E5">S^{m(3)}_{n}\left(z,\gamma\right)=S^{m(1)}_{n}\left(z,\gamma\right)+\mathrm{i} S^{m(2)}_{n}\left(z,\gamma\right),S^{m(4)}_{n}\left(z,\gamma\right)=S^{m(1)}_{n}\left(z,\gamma\right)-\mathrm{i} S^{m(2)}_{n}\left(z,\gamma\right)</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
</paragraph>
 
