<subsection xml:id="C30.S11.SS3">
<title>Asymptotic Behavior</title>        
  
<para xml:id="C30.S11.SS3.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="11" xml:id="C30.S11.SS3.p1.s1">
For fixed <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C30.S11.SS3.p1.m1">\gamma</Math> , as <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C30.S11.SS3.p1.m2">z\to\infty</Math> in the sector <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C30.S11.SS3.p1.m3">|\operatorname{ph}z|\leq\pi-\delta</Math> ( <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C30.S11.SS3.p1.m4">&lt;\pi</Math> ), <Math equation-number="30.11.6" mode="display" xml:id="C30.S11.E6">S^{m(j)}_{n}\left(z,\gamma\right)=\begin{cases}\psi_{n}^{(j)}(\gamma z)+O\left (z^{-2}e^{|\Im z|}\right),&amp;j=1,2,\\ \psi_{n}^{(j)}(\gamma z)\left(1+O\left(z^{-1}\right)\right),&amp;j=3,4.\end{cases</Math> }
</sentence>

</para>
 
<para xml:id="C30.S11.SS3.p2">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="12" xml:id="C30.S11.SS3.p2.s1">
For asymptotic expansions in negative powers of <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C30.S11.SS3.p2.m1">z</Math> seeMeixner and Schäfke (1954, p. 293).
</sentence>

</para>

 
</subsection>
 
<subsection xml:id="C30.S11.SS4">
<title>Wronskian</title>        
  
<para xml:id="C30.S11.SS4.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="13" xml:id="C30.S11.SS4.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="30.11.7" mode="display" xml:id="C30.S11.E7">\mathscr{W}\left\{S^{m(1)}_{n}\left(z,\gamma\right),S^{m(2)}_{n}\left(z,\gamma \right)\right\}=\frac{1}{\gamma(z^{2}-1)}</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
</subsection>
 
<subsection xml:id="C30.S11.SS5">
<title>Connection with the <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C30.S11.SS5.m1">\mathit{Ps}</Math> and <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C30.S11.SS5.m2">\mathit{Qs}</Math> Functions</title>        
 
 
<para xml:id="C30.S11.SS5.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="14" xml:id="C30.S11.SS5.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="30.11.8" mode="display" xml:id="C30.S11.E8">S^{m(1)}_{n}\left(z,\gamma\right)=K_{n}^{m}(\gamma)\mathit{Ps}^{m}_{n}\left(z, \gamma^{2}\right),</Math> <Math equation-number="30.11.9" mode="display" xml:id="C30.S11.E9">S^{m(2)}_{n}\left(z,\gamma\right)=\frac{(n-m)!}{(n+m)!}\frac{(-1)^{m+1}\mathit {Qs}^{m}_{n}\left(z,\gamma^{2}\right)}{\gamma K_{n}^{m}(\gamma)A_{n}^{m}( \gamma^{2})A_{n}^{-m}(\gamma^{2})},</Math> where <Math equation-number="30.11.10" mode="display" xml:id="C30.S11.E10">K_{n}^{m}(\gamma)=\frac{\sqrt{\pi}}{2}\left(\frac{\gamma}{2}\right)^{m}\frac{( -1)^{m}a_{n,\frac{1}{2}(m-n)}^{-m}(\gamma^{2})}{\Gamma\left(\frac{3}{2}+m \right)A_{n}^{-m}(\gamma^{2})\mathsf{Ps}^{m}_{n}\left(0,\gamma^{2}\right)}, if n-m even,</Math> or <Math equation-number="30.11.11" mode="display" xml:id="C30.S11.E11">K_{n}^{m}(\gamma)=\frac{\sqrt{\pi}}{2}\left(\frac{\gamma}{2}\right)^{m+1}\* \frac{(-1)^{m}a_{n,\frac{1}{2}(m-n+1)}^{-m}(\gamma^{2})}{\Gamma\left(\frac{5}{ 2}+m\right)A_{n}^{-m}(\gamma^{2})(\left.\ifrac{\mathrm{d}\mathsf{Ps}^{m}_{n}(z ,\gamma^{2})}{\mathrm{d}z}\right|_{z=0})}, if n-m odd</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>

 
</subsection>
 
<subsection xml:id="C30.S11.SS6">
<title>Integral Representations</title>        
 
 
<para xml:id="C30.S11.SS6.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="15" xml:id="C30.S11.SS6.p1.s1">
When <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C30.S11.SS6.p1.m1">z\in\mathbb{C}\setminus(-\infty,1]</Math> <Math equation-number="30.11.12" mode="display" xml:id="C30.S11.E12">A_{n}^{-m}(\gamma^{2})S^{m(1)}_{n}\left(z,\gamma\right)=\frac{1}{2}{\mathrm{i} ^{m+n}}\gamma^{m}\frac{(n-m)!}{(n+m)!}z^{m}(1-z^{-2})^{\frac{1}{2}m}\*\int_{-1 }^{1}e^{-\mathrm{i}\gamma zt}(1-t^{2})^{\frac{1}{2}m}\mathsf{Ps}^{m}_{n}\left( t,\gamma^{2}\right)\mathrm{d}t</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
<para xml:id="C30.S11.SS6.p2">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="16" xml:id="C30.S11.SS6.p2.s1">
For further relations see Arscott (1964b, §8.6),Connett et al. (1993), Erdélyi et al. (1955, §16.13),Meixner and Schäfke (1954), and Meixner et al. (1980, §3.1).
</sentence>

</para>
 
